result.execSummary:
The defendant Arthur Joseph Dashner Jr. was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • False Imprisonment [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.30.
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Arthur Joseph Dashner in court with attorney Chris A. Gramstrup.  Kelly J Mcknight appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 15CF110,15CF178,15Cf188 are SEHR 16CF67 and 16CF68 for SEH. State complied with Vic rights. no response. no agreement for seh. no joint recommendation. DA filed a recommendation. PSI was filed. 16CF188 was the only case that didnt occur in the presence of children. DA does have prior record. no corrections to PSI from either party. Atty comments- some offenses occurred in the presence of children, but is a devoted father, intelligent person, would not object to getting GED, good relationship with father, AODA issues are a factor, willing to address the issue, Stable living history, good work ethic, can support himself and family. does have remorse. AODA, Domestic Violence assessment. Atty would think longer probation but shorter init confinement. 1 year init 2 years extended. 16CF67 1 year init 3 years extended. 68 1 years init 1 year extended to run concurrent together., 3 years inti and 6 years extended. Sentence credit submitted to court. 15CF178 count 2 was DRI. Today getting sentenced on 3 domestic batteries. Ct agrees with both sides, will go to prison for a while. SEE OFFER TO SETTLE.
